04:55.291 --> 04:58.041
Doug wanted to invite
Lindsay Penn.

04:58.041 --> 04:59.375
- Who?
- Natalie's replacement.

04:59.375 --> 05:02.417
The actress we put
in Waterfall 3.

05:02.417 --> 05:05.166
He thought it would be
a...touching handover

05:05.166 --> 05:07.500
to have her here.

05:07.500 --> 05:10.250
Bastard--
he didn't shed a tear,

05:10.250 --> 05:14.291
not for his child,
not for her,

05:14.291 --> 05:15.125
not a tear.

05:15.125 --> 05:17.583
I need a favor.

05:17.583 --> 05:19.125
Anything.
What is it?

05:19.125 --> 05:21.083
There's a doctor
at Sloan Kettering.

05:21.083 --> 05:23.125
Does the doctor
have a name?

05:23.125 --> 05:25.917
Sharon Bergstein.
She's a neurosurgeon.

05:27.667 --> 05:30.333
I need her to do something
she doesn't want to do.

05:30.333 --> 05:31.375
[engine turning over]

05:31.375 --> 05:32.709
I'll get back to you.

05:35.000 --> 05:38.208
[cell phone ringing]

05:43.083 --> 05:44.667
Yeah.

05:44.667 --> 05:46.500
[Jackson]
Where's the goddamn roscoe?

05:46.500 --> 05:49.000
- [Ray] What?
-  [Jackson] The boom stick.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.083
- [Jackson] The banger.
- The gun?

05:51.083 --> 05:53.166
Yes. Jesus.

05:53.166 --> 05:55.125
- [Ray] You'll get it.
- Yeah, well, you got

05:55.125 --> 05:56.083
until tonight, or else
I'll bring back charges

05:56.083 --> 05:58.959
against your daughter.

06:13.834 --> 06:16.625
- [clicks tongue, sighs]
- [buzzer sounds in distance]

06:17.500 --> 06:20.041
[buzzer sounds,
door squeaks open]

06:20.041 --> 06:25.542
[indistinct chatter]

06:25.542 --> 06:27.625
[buzzer sounds]

06:29.125 --> 06:31.041
Morning.

06:31.041 --> 06:34.208
Ha ha. Got to thank you
for the cards.

06:34.208 --> 06:35.625
And the Tab.

06:36.625 --> 06:38.834
Do you want
a lawyer present?

06:41.750 --> 06:42.542
I'm an old man.

06:42.542 --> 06:46.208
So...you don't need
an attorney.

06:46.208 --> 06:48.000
You're a young guy.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.542
- I don't follow.
- You don't want me.

06:50.542 --> 06:52.250
Careers aren't made
on white-haired gentlemen

06:52.250 --> 06:54.208
with long rap sheets.

06:54.208 --> 06:57.709
You got something better?

06:57.709 --> 07:00.208
I got facts
you'd be interested in.

07:00.208 --> 07:02.083
I see.

07:02.083 --> 07:04.583
Yeah. You give me
a chance...

07:04.583 --> 07:08.583
I can lead you
to the truth of many things.

07:10.250 --> 07:12.250
So you're an innocent man.

07:12.250 --> 07:14.583
- "Innocent"?
- Hmm.

07:14.583 --> 07:15.375
No.

07:15.375 --> 07:17.291
I done a lot of bad
things.

07:17.291 --> 07:20.041
Never killed
no black people.

07:20.041 --> 07:21.917
I'm in with
the black community

07:21.917 --> 07:23.250
through the female side.

07:23.250 --> 07:26.709
But I, uh...

07:26.709 --> 07:27.834
I'm not gonna
hide nothin' from ya.

07:27.834 --> 07:29.750
Good.

07:31.291 --> 07:33.834
I read your file.

07:33.834 --> 07:35.083
Uh-huh.

07:35.083 --> 07:37.250
20 years in Walpole.

07:37.250 --> 07:38.417
The time I spent
in Walpole

07:38.417 --> 07:42.667
was for a crime
I did not commit.

07:42.667 --> 07:45.542
Crime you arrested me for--
I didn't do that neither.

07:45.542 --> 07:48.125
- Really?
- Really.

07:48.125 --> 07:50.834
But I could tell you...

07:50.834 --> 07:54.333
who really shot Sully Sullivan
between the eyes.

07:54.333 --> 07:55.625
Yeah?

07:55.625 --> 07:58.291
Who shot Sean Walker
the same way.

07:58.291 --> 08:01.333
I can tell you about
who killed Cookie Brown,

08:01.333 --> 08:03.458
about who killed
that Boston Globe  reporter.

08:03.458 --> 08:04.500
I'd be interested
in all that.

08:04.500 --> 08:08.625
Plus who killed
Frank Barnes...

08:08.625 --> 08:10.208
if you let me go.

08:10.208 --> 08:13.667
If I can make a case.

08:18.583 --> 08:21.166
It saddens me to say this...

08:21.166 --> 08:22.417
[exhales deeply]

08:22.417 --> 08:24.458
...but, uh...

08:24.458 --> 08:27.375
all those people--
Sully,

08:27.375 --> 08:29.834
Cookie Brown,
that poor girl,

08:29.834 --> 08:32.917
Frank Barnes--

08:32.917 --> 08:35.083
all of 'em were killed
by my son...

08:35.083 --> 08:38.583
Ray Donovan.

08:41.709 --> 08:43.166
- Morning, Ray.
- Hey, Bunch.

08:43.166 --> 08:45.250
Drinking?

08:45.250 --> 08:48.417
Sure.

08:55.667 --> 08:57.917
Where's the gun, Daryll?

09:03.166 --> 09:06.542
Ray, I don't think
I can do this.

09:06.542 --> 09:07.792
No?

09:07.792 --> 09:10.083
He's our father, man.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.125
And?

09:13.417 --> 09:16.709
And...I'm gonna go
down to the police station

09:16.709 --> 09:19.417
and tell the truth.

09:22.542 --> 09:24.375
That's your big plan?

09:24.375 --> 09:27.500
Turn yourself in?

09:27.500 --> 09:30.208
- I pulled the trigger, Ray.
- Don't be a fucking idiot.

09:30.208 --> 09:32.250
[Ray] Get yourself clear
of this while you still can.

09:32.250 --> 09:33.709
You go down
to the D.A.'s office,

09:33.709 --> 09:35.583
and you tell 'em
Mickey shot Barnes.

09:35.583 --> 09:36.417
- You understand?
- Ray, why are we doing this

09:36.417 --> 09:40.166
to Mickey, man?
Why?

09:40.166 --> 09:42.041
Because you and I both know

09:42.041 --> 09:45.083
the minute Mickey feels the
pinch, he's gonna turn you in.

09:45.083 --> 09:48.083
Don't think he won't,
Daryll.

09:48.083 --> 09:50.667
He's a fuckin' rat.

09:50.667 --> 09:51.917
Always has been.

09:53.625 --> 09:56.917
- [glass thuds]
- Remember that.

10:06.208 --> 10:10.291
Take the gun...
and throw it in the river.

10:10.291 --> 10:12.417
And Bridge
will get pulled back in,

10:12.417 --> 10:13.750
and Ray
will fuckin' kill me.

10:13.750 --> 10:16.250
I'd throw the gun
in the fuckin' river.

10:16.250 --> 10:18.959
Ray's just gonna have

10:18.959 --> 10:21.166
to figure out somethin' else
for Bridge.

10:23.291 --> 10:26.333
[softly] You know,
I could, uh--I...

10:26.333 --> 10:27.166
could always tell the truth.

10:27.166 --> 10:29.917
For Mickey?

10:32.250 --> 10:33.125
Fuck that.

10:33.125 --> 10:35.041
[chuckles]

10:37.291 --> 10:40.208
No weapon, no murder charge.

10:41.834 --> 10:44.542
Take the gun,
throw it in the river,

10:44.542 --> 10:46.250
and be done with it.

10:46.250 --> 10:48.208
[slurps]

10:52.875 --> 10:57.083
Frank Barnes was on
Ray's payroll for years.

10:57.083 --> 10:58.750
You didn't know that,
huh?

10:58.750 --> 11:00.083
- I did not.
- [smacks lips] For years.

11:00.083 --> 11:02.458
Years.

11:02.458 --> 11:03.583
So he and Ray were close.

11:03.583 --> 11:07.792
Not that they
liked each other.

11:07.792 --> 11:11.458
But when, uh, he took down
Sokolov and his gang,

11:11.458 --> 11:12.417
Frank got greedy
and started selling

11:12.417 --> 11:15.291
the heroin
and the fentanyl

11:15.291 --> 11:16.750
that they lifted
from the bust...

11:16.750 --> 11:18.333
- Hmm.
- ...using Avi...

11:18.333 --> 11:20.959
as his distribution.

11:20.959 --> 11:22.125
Who's Ray's associate?

11:22.125 --> 11:24.542
Yeah.

11:24.542 --> 11:27.000
Did, uh--did Ray
know about this?

11:27.000 --> 11:30.333
Sure.
Ray knows everything.

11:30.333 --> 11:32.083
But he said not a peep.

11:32.083 --> 11:34.083
He let that pass.

11:34.083 --> 11:36.500
But when the DEA
got wind of it,

11:36.500 --> 11:39.166
Frank needed
a real favor--

11:39.166 --> 11:41.208
get rid of Avi Rudin.

11:41.208 --> 11:42.500
What was that about?

11:42.500 --> 11:44.458
Well, you see,
Avi had become

11:44.458 --> 11:47.166
a full-blown addict
and a real liability,

11:47.166 --> 11:50.208
and Frank wanted
the Jew out.

11:50.208 --> 11:53.583
He told Ray,
"It's him or me."

11:54.625 --> 11:57.959
But Ray was loyal to the Jew,

11:57.959 --> 12:00.625
so Ray fucking killed Frank.

12:00.625 --> 12:04.709
How do you know that...
he actually killed Frank?

12:04.709 --> 12:06.250
He told me.

12:06.250 --> 12:09.208
- He told you.
- Hand on the Bible.

12:09.208 --> 12:12.166
He said he lured him
to this quiet parking lot

12:12.166 --> 12:13.875
east of Chinatown

12:13.875 --> 12:18.458
on the promise of delivering
Avi Rudin's dead body.

12:18.458 --> 12:22.333
And there in the parking lot,
under a full moon...

12:22.333 --> 12:24.834
he led Frank
to the back of his car

12:24.834 --> 12:27.000
and blew his brains out.

12:27.291 --> 12:29.458
[smacks lips]

12:33.959 --> 12:36.834
[whispers indistinctly]

12:36.834 --> 12:39.041
[buzzer sounds, door opens]

12:40.417 --> 12:43.000
So...parking lot.

12:43.000 --> 12:45.750
- [door closes]
- Did he mention where exactly?

12:45.750 --> 12:48.250
Oh, yeah.
I think he said it was, uh,

12:48.250 --> 12:50.083
the corner of Spring
and College.

12:50.083 --> 12:51.750
Ah...

12:51.750 --> 12:53.750
I haven't been down there
in a long time.

12:53.750 --> 12:55.458
Yeah, it's been a while

12:55.458 --> 12:56.959
since I've heard anyone
call that area Chinatown.

12:56.959 --> 13:00.000
Yeah, I know.
All the good chink restaurants

13:00.000 --> 13:00.834
are up in
San Gabriel now.

13:00.834 --> 13:03.875
Not that it's
my favorite cuisine.

13:03.875 --> 13:06.917
- [Jackson] Hmm.
- High sodium.

13:06.917 --> 13:09.917
So...corner of
Spring and College...

13:09.917 --> 13:13.125
Yeah. There might be
some blood out there.

13:13.125 --> 13:15.375
Have your guys
check it out.

13:15.375 --> 13:18.667
- We'll look into it.
- If all this turns true...

13:18.667 --> 13:20.667
you'll let me out?

13:20.667 --> 13:23.000
If it sticks, yes.

13:23.000 --> 13:24.792
Trust me, you crack this,

13:24.792 --> 13:28.125
you'll be the next
Chief of the FBI.

13:28.125 --> 13:30.125
- [chuckles]
- Well, who knows?

13:30.125 --> 13:31.917
- Even maybe governor.
- Ah.

13:31.917 --> 13:33.500
That's been done.

13:33.500 --> 13:36.458
Books will be written,
movies.

13:39.041 --> 13:43.625
No, the kid got sick,
so I took him to the hospital.

13:44.834 --> 13:47.917
They just gave him an IV,
and they sent him home.

13:47.917 --> 13:49.125
Yeah.

13:49.125 --> 13:51.750
[whimpers]

13:51.750 --> 13:54.375
There's nothing can be done.

13:55.583 --> 13:59.083
Yeah, I know I missed it
again, but I'll be there later.

13:59.083 --> 14:02.333
Jesus Christ, this is--
this is family, for fuck's sake!

14:02.333 --> 14:04.875
[vomiting]

14:06.792 --> 14:09.417
Kid? Kid.

14:09.417 --> 14:11.333
We got to get you
back to the hospital.

14:11.333 --> 14:12.333
- No!
- Come on.

14:12.333 --> 14:14.625
- [retches, coughs]
- All right, come on.

14:14.625 --> 14:16.166
- No.
- You need a doctor.

14:16.166 --> 14:17.750
No, no doctor, just...

14:17.750 --> 14:19.667
[sniffles]

14:19.667 --> 14:22.500
[mumbling] Just--just give me--
give me your hand.

14:22.500 --> 14:24.000
What?

14:24.000 --> 14:28.667
Put your hand
on my head, please.

14:28.667 --> 14:30.792
- Got any pills?
- No.

14:30.792 --> 14:33.834
- You got no pain pills?
- I'm out.

14:33.834 --> 14:36.208
[weakly]
Just put--just put your hand--

14:36.208 --> 14:38.125
put your hand on my...

14:39.542 --> 14:41.375
[sniffles, groans]

14:41.375 --> 14:45.208
[crying]

14:45.208 --> 14:48.208
♪ somber music ♪

14:48.208 --> 14:53.166
♪♪♪

14:53.166 --> 14:55.375
[continues crying,
sniffling]

14:58.125 --> 15:01.166
[whimpering, crying]

15:01.166 --> 15:06.041
♪♪♪

15:13.125 --> 15:16.500
[Smitty crying, panting]

15:18.250 --> 15:23.125
♪♪♪

15:36.375 --> 15:38.542
[sighs]

15:39.625 --> 15:42.375
I need your help.

15:42.375 --> 15:44.125
Would it surprise you
to learn

15:44.125 --> 15:45.667
that this is not new
for me?

15:45.667 --> 15:47.834
That kid's not gonna
make it a week

15:47.834 --> 15:49.750
without the surgery.

15:50.792 --> 15:53.458
A year ago,
a guy broke into my home,

15:53.458 --> 15:56.083
came into my bedroom, stood
over me saying the rosary

15:56.083 --> 15:58.250
because he wanted me
to save his son.

15:58.250 --> 15:58.875
I can set you up.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.959
Private operating room,

16:00.959 --> 16:03.083
your own people--
whatever you need.

16:03.083 --> 16:06.667
[scoffs] What you're
asking me to do is immoral,

16:06.667 --> 16:09.166
and...it's illegal.

16:09.709 --> 16:11.875
No one will know.

16:11.875 --> 16:14.542
Somebody always knows.

16:19.375 --> 16:21.709
That's my number.
When you change your mind.

16:21.709 --> 16:23.083
- I won't change my mind.
- Take it.

16:23.083 --> 16:26.625
- For when you do.
- [car door closes]

16:33.834 --> 16:35.709
There you go, miss.

16:35.709 --> 16:37.417
[Sharon] Thank you.

16:41.792 --> 16:45.750
[indistinct chatter]

17:01.375 --> 17:04.291
[dog panting]

17:05.458 --> 17:07.750
Hey, Dog.

17:07.750 --> 17:09.542
Hey. Hey, big boy.

17:09.542 --> 17:10.417
Come on, come on.

17:10.417 --> 17:13.125
Hey. [smooches, whistles]
Come on!

17:13.125 --> 17:15.083
Come on.

17:15.083 --> 17:18.125
♪ dark music ♪

17:18.125 --> 17:22.250
♪♪♪

17:43.959 --> 17:46.041
[Stanley] You should never bend
an electrical cord, otherwise--

17:46.041 --> 17:47.875
- [electricity buzzes]
- [woman] Aah!

17:47.875 --> 17:49.375
- [laughter]
- [Stanley] Told ya!

17:49.375 --> 17:51.875
- [Jack] What happened?
- [Ray] Mom?

17:51.875 --> 17:54.125
[Helen] Stanley was showing us
how not to get a shock.

17:54.125 --> 17:55.083
- [laughter]
- [Stanley] Will you put

17:55.083 --> 17:57.750
some clothes on?
My wife's here.

17:57.750 --> 17:59.542
[Helen] Mind your own
business, Stanley.

17:59.542 --> 18:01.041
[laughter on television]

18:01.041 --> 18:03.000
[Stanley] What if
the towel slips?

18:03.000 --> 18:05.625
[Helen] Mind your own
business, Stanley.

18:05.625 --> 18:07.542
Jack, you have some
shaving cream on your face.

18:07.542 --> 18:09.750
- Oh, thank you.
-  [Chrissy]  No, Jack!

18:09.750 --> 18:10.875
[laughter, show fade]

18:10.875 --> 18:14.625
♪ dark music ♪

18:14.625 --> 18:19.417
♪♪♪

18:25.917 --> 18:30.959
[footsteps approaching]

18:30.959 --> 18:33.375
[Conor] Dad?

18:39.959 --> 18:42.750
It looks so fucking weird.

18:42.750 --> 18:43.417
[softly] Yeah.

18:47.208 --> 18:49.125
What happened
to your arm?

18:49.125 --> 18:50.792
- Nothing.
- Doesn't look like nothing.

18:50.792 --> 18:51.875
- Con.
- Yeah?

18:51.875 --> 18:54.208
[inhales deeply]

18:54.208 --> 18:57.333
You sure this is
what you want?

18:57.333 --> 18:59.250
- Yeah.
- None of us served.

18:59.250 --> 19:00.709
Uncle Mac did.

19:00.709 --> 19:03.875
Uncle Mac died
in Vietnam, Conor.

19:03.875 --> 19:06.000
It's what I want.

19:09.041 --> 19:10.291
All right.

19:15.000 --> 19:18.458
[car horn honks]

19:18.458 --> 19:21.417
[siren wailing in distance]

19:32.125 --> 19:36.333
[cell phone ringing]

19:36.333 --> 19:38.250
- Yeah.
- [Jay] Need you by my side,

19:38.250 --> 19:39.375
Daryll Donovan.

19:39.375 --> 19:41.333
I need you by my side.

19:43.291 --> 19:46.333
♪ dramatic music ♪

19:46.333 --> 19:50.458
♪♪♪

19:59.166 --> 20:00.500
Thank you.

20:00.500 --> 20:02.625
[Conor] Thank you.

20:02.625 --> 20:07.500
♪♪♪

20:17.875 --> 20:20.208
Want to go get a beer?

20:20.208 --> 20:21.291
Now?

20:21.291 --> 20:22.959
Yeah, let's, uh...

20:22.959 --> 20:24.834
let's go get a beer
and talk.

20:24.834 --> 20:26.458
Dad, I got to get
back to school.

20:26.458 --> 20:28.000
I still have finals.

20:28.000 --> 20:29.667
I'll drive you up
later today.

20:29.667 --> 20:31.500
No. There's a bus.
I ju--I just want to get back.

20:35.125 --> 20:36.458
You sure?

20:39.166 --> 20:41.208
Can I ask you something?

20:41.208 --> 20:44.083
Yeah. What's up?

20:44.083 --> 20:46.667
What do you
think of me?

20:46.667 --> 20:48.542
What do you mean
what do I think of you?

20:48.542 --> 20:50.041
What do you think of me?

20:52.583 --> 20:54.250
You're my kid.

20:54.250 --> 20:55.625
You think I'm a fucking
idiot, don't you?

20:55.625 --> 20:57.792
No, I don't think
you're an idiot, Conor.

20:57.792 --> 20:59.667
- I think you're my son.
- Fuck that, I get that.

20:59.667 --> 21:01.750
But you don't
respect me, do you?

21:01.750 --> 21:03.750
- Of course I do.
- No, you don't.

21:03.750 --> 21:05.959
You think I'm weak
and stupid.

21:05.959 --> 21:08.250
Conor, listen--

21:08.250 --> 21:10.417
You know,
it's better this way.

21:10.417 --> 21:12.291
After the Marines,
you'll see what I am.

21:12.291 --> 21:15.834
- I see what you are now.
- No, you don't.

21:15.834 --> 21:17.417
You fucking don't.
I'm gonna be a soldier.

21:17.417 --> 21:19.333
When I get back,
you're gonna work for me.

21:19.333 --> 21:21.291
That's who I am.

21:31.583 --> 21:33.625
A rich, successful
black man is a target.

21:33.625 --> 21:35.792
- Who told me that?
- I did.

21:35.792 --> 21:36.792
And if I listened
to my father,

21:36.792 --> 21:39.208
I'd still be making
the fucking White House.

21:39.208 --> 21:40.417
Told me to never
leave that sitcom--

21:40.417 --> 21:43.458
there'd be checks in the mail
till my dyin' day.

21:43.458 --> 21:45.291
Fuck that.

21:45.291 --> 21:47.375
- Check that out.
- What?

21:47.375 --> 21:50.458
- Um, what--
- No, no. That.

21:55.208 --> 21:59.125
- Um...
- Look at that.

21:59.125 --> 22:01.917
Yeah...
[chuckles]

22:02.959 --> 22:04.625
Uh, okay, so what--what's--
What is all this?

22:04.625 --> 22:08.375
You a goddamn producer
for a White House production.

22:08.375 --> 22:11.834
Can't have my man sitting out
in some fucking cubicle.

22:11.834 --> 22:14.041
- Shit!
- [chuckles]

22:14.041 --> 22:16.375
Wow. Uh...

22:16.375 --> 22:19.625
yeah, Jay, this is cool,
man, but my father--

22:19.625 --> 22:22.417
Daryll, you know shit
about me.

22:22.417 --> 22:26.125
I'm gonna keep you close.

22:26.125 --> 22:28.291
But the truth is,
I like how you operate.

22:28.291 --> 22:31.667
Hmm?
I see you as an asset.

22:35.250 --> 22:37.667
[stammers] Jay, w-what
are you asking me?

22:37.667 --> 22:40.500
Testify against
your father, Daryll.

22:40.500 --> 22:42.333
Tell Jackson Holt
what he needs to know.

22:42.333 --> 22:43.959
All right, you, me--

22:43.959 --> 22:45.750
we would've
just made a phone call,

22:45.750 --> 22:47.458
made things right.

22:47.458 --> 22:49.542
Your father,
he comes along,

22:49.542 --> 22:52.500
everything
goes upside down.

22:56.667 --> 22:58.959
- [chuckles nervously]
- Just tell the truth, brother,

22:58.959 --> 23:00.667
and all this...

23:03.417 --> 23:05.959
[snaps fingers]
...is yours.

23:31.875 --> 23:33.792
Hi.

23:34.917 --> 23:37.417
Hi.

23:40.667 --> 23:43.583
So I called
the landlord.

23:43.583 --> 23:45.959
We're good
to let the lease go.

23:45.959 --> 23:48.583
Okay.

23:51.083 --> 23:53.417
So we can leave next week.

23:57.041 --> 24:00.875
I'm just, uh...

24:00.875 --> 24:02.667
getting some things
in order for Ray.

24:09.375 --> 24:11.709
I promise we'll work it out.

24:11.709 --> 24:12.625
Let's just get out of L.A.

24:12.625 --> 24:16.250
Let's just leave
all this shit behind.

24:22.208 --> 24:25.458
[sighs]
I'll make you two some lunch.

24:35.917 --> 24:39.542
[sighs]

24:39.542 --> 24:41.625
So how you doing
this week?

24:41.625 --> 24:43.458
Good.

24:43.458 --> 24:45.542
Really good.

24:45.542 --> 24:47.792
- Really?
- Yeah.

24:47.792 --> 24:49.834
How's the Zoloft
treating you?

24:49.834 --> 24:51.583
Not taking it.

24:51.583 --> 24:53.542
I see.

24:53.542 --> 24:56.166
What'd you do
to your arm?

24:56.166 --> 24:57.458
Ah, it's just...

24:57.458 --> 24:59.792
accident
working out in the yard.

25:11.667 --> 25:15.500
Ah. I was in the military
for 21 years.

25:15.500 --> 25:18.375
Does that surprise you?

25:18.375 --> 25:19.667
[groans softly]

25:19.667 --> 25:22.458
I saw you on the news
this morning

25:22.458 --> 25:25.458
at that movie star's
funeral.

25:25.458 --> 25:26.375
Yeah.

25:26.375 --> 25:29.291
How did that
make you feel--

25:29.291 --> 25:30.834
her dying?

25:35.792 --> 25:37.542
She was young, you know?

25:37.542 --> 25:40.291
I bet you go
to a lot of those.

25:40.291 --> 25:42.750
I've been to a ton.

25:42.750 --> 25:45.000
So hard, you know,
to feel it.

25:45.000 --> 25:46.959
[inhales deeply]
Hard to...

25:46.959 --> 25:49.875
allow yourself to feel
anything, really, right?

25:51.375 --> 25:53.458
I don't know.

25:53.458 --> 25:55.208
Sometimes.

25:55.208 --> 25:57.125
What about your wife?

25:57.125 --> 25:58.041
Does it make you
think about Abby?

25:58.041 --> 25:59.542
Sure.

25:59.542 --> 26:02.417
Would you like
to talk about that?

26:02.417 --> 26:04.125
What?

26:05.875 --> 26:08.291
No. I'm...

26:08.291 --> 26:11.125
- ...fine.
- Mm-hmm.

26:18.041 --> 26:20.750
So this is our last
session.

26:20.750 --> 26:22.417
Yeah.

26:22.417 --> 26:25.750
How does that
make you feel?

26:27.417 --> 26:30.750
I don't know.
I guess I'm, uh...

26:30.750 --> 26:34.208
glad to be putting
my probation behind me.

26:34.208 --> 26:38.125
[softly]
I see.

26:38.125 --> 26:40.333
I'm just gonna...
talk freely for a minute,

26:40.333 --> 26:43.291
if you don't mind.

26:43.291 --> 26:45.750
You're the boss.

26:48.834 --> 26:52.500
You're a severely
traumatized person, Ray.

26:52.500 --> 26:54.375
You blame yourself
for the trauma

26:54.375 --> 26:57.458
inflicted on you
by others.

26:57.458 --> 27:00.250
You control it that way.

27:00.250 --> 27:02.834
You make it your own
that way.

27:02.834 --> 27:04.417
I know you know about

27:04.417 --> 27:07.083
Post traumatic
stress disorder, right?

27:07.083 --> 27:09.417
I mean, that's a real thing.

27:09.417 --> 27:13.375
It's destructive,
and it kills people, okay?

27:14.709 --> 27:17.375
And you have that.

27:17.375 --> 27:19.667
And it needs to be
treated.

27:21.208 --> 27:23.917
I thought that's what
we were doing here.

27:23.917 --> 27:24.583
[scoffs]

27:24.583 --> 27:27.667
You're smarter than that.

27:28.959 --> 27:32.083
These are things you got
to work on your entire life.

27:32.083 --> 27:34.375
But you need tools
for that, Ray--

27:34.375 --> 27:37.750
group therapy, medication,

27:37.750 --> 27:40.458
one-on-one therapy.

27:40.458 --> 27:42.417
Now, I know you don't want
to hear this right now,

27:42.417 --> 27:43.417
but that's what it takes
to learn how to forgive others

27:43.417 --> 27:46.417
for what they did to you...

27:46.417 --> 27:48.917
to forgive yourself.

27:51.166 --> 27:53.375
Forgive myself for what?

27:53.375 --> 27:57.000
You can be helped.

27:57.000 --> 27:58.834
Trust me.

27:58.834 --> 28:00.667
[Father O'Connor]
Trust me, Raymond.

28:00.667 --> 28:03.667
♪ dark music ♪

28:03.667 --> 28:08.000
♪♪♪

28:08.000 --> 28:09.166
I'm good.

28:09.166 --> 28:11.583
[whispers] So...

28:11.583 --> 28:13.667
I think I got...

28:16.375 --> 28:18.083
I think I got
my whole anger--

28:18.083 --> 28:19.875
anger thing under control,
so I...

28:19.875 --> 28:23.667
want to thank you for that,
you know.

28:23.667 --> 28:26.000
Appreciate it.

28:27.375 --> 28:29.375
So...

28:29.375 --> 28:33.041
[exhales deeply]

28:33.041 --> 28:34.041
Thanks.

28:39.709 --> 28:41.875
[door closes]

28:41.875 --> 28:46.375
♪♪♪

28:46.375 --> 28:48.291
[Marty] Rumors are
already swirling

28:48.291 --> 28:50.375
that Doug Landry has
chosen actress Lindsay Penn

28:50.375 --> 28:53.333
to replace Natalie James
in the  Waterfall  series.

28:53.333 --> 28:54.917
Landry, heading today
to New York

28:54.917 --> 28:56.917
for the yearly
Pacific Board meeting,

28:56.917 --> 28:58.792
denied the replacement
has been chosen.

28:58.792 --> 29:00.208
Marty's doing
a fucking special.

29:00.208 --> 29:02.959
[Marty] The new director
of the  Waterfall  franchise...

29:02.959 --> 29:04.834
- [Marty continues]
- What's that?

29:04.834 --> 29:08.291
I finished
my anger management thing.

29:08.291 --> 29:09.875
- You feel rehabilitated?
- [Marty] We can guarantee

29:09.875 --> 29:13.000
- that confirmation is coming.
- Sure.

29:13.000 --> 29:13.625
[Marty] Now let's go
to Sandy Gagic

29:13.625 --> 29:16.417
for a special report.

29:16.417 --> 29:19.959
[Sandy] A bully for hire
with a baseball bat in hand

29:19.959 --> 29:21.583
managed to insinuate himself

29:21.583 --> 29:22.792
into Hollywood's
inner circles,

29:22.792 --> 29:24.875
allied himself
with stars and moguls

29:24.875 --> 29:28.083
who were so terrified,
so needy,

29:28.083 --> 29:29.792
and so desperate,
they hired a thug

29:29.792 --> 29:30.750
so they could sleep
at night.

29:30.750 --> 29:33.667
But the fairy dust
has worn off,

29:33.667 --> 29:35.917
and now with the greatest
talent of her generation

29:35.917 --> 29:36.875
found dead in his apartment

29:36.875 --> 29:40.000
and his client list
coming forward

29:40.000 --> 29:41.917
to admit he exploited
their worst fears,

29:41.917 --> 29:46.333
Ray Donovan's career
in Hollywood is over.

29:46.333 --> 29:48.000
Asshole.

29:50.917 --> 29:54.500
A few clients called today,
said they're leaving.

29:54.500 --> 29:55.375
You want the list?

29:55.375 --> 29:57.667
Nah.

29:57.667 --> 30:00.709
They're all fuckin' assholes.

30:10.959 --> 30:12.250
Take it.

30:14.291 --> 30:17.375
We all going to hell.

30:21.750 --> 30:23.417
[cell phone vibrates]

30:24.625 --> 30:28.500
[door opens, closes]

30:28.500 --> 30:30.083
Yeah.

30:30.083 --> 30:31.667
You motherfucker.

30:31.667 --> 30:33.583
Who'd you call?

30:33.583 --> 30:36.125
- Doesn't matter.
- [Sharon] They're forcing me

30:36.125 --> 30:38.834
- to resign my chair.
- Yeah?

30:38.834 --> 30:42.208
What'd you do?
What the fuck did you do?

30:42.208 --> 30:44.417
[Ray] I asked you to help.

30:44.417 --> 30:46.875
They're threatening
to defund the entire program.

30:46.875 --> 30:50.583
There's a way
to make that stop.

30:52.834 --> 30:56.166
Do you have any idea
what you're doing?

30:56.166 --> 30:57.166
Yeah, I do.

30:57.166 --> 30:59.250
You're the fucking devil.
You know that?

30:59.250 --> 31:03.291
You're the most immoral piece
of shit that I have ever--

31:03.291 --> 31:05.959
I'll send a car
to pick you up.

31:05.959 --> 31:07.125
[cell phone beeps]

31:16.709 --> 31:19.709
I need you to fly
to New York.

31:19.709 --> 31:21.709
Uh...call Archie Leach.

31:21.709 --> 31:23.458
There's a clinic
on the Upper East Side.

31:23.458 --> 31:26.625
What's this about?

31:26.625 --> 31:27.709
We're gonna get that kid
the surgery.

31:27.709 --> 31:31.500
♪ soft music ♪

31:31.500 --> 31:36.625
♪♪♪

31:42.875 --> 31:45.542
[cell phone ringing]

31:45.542 --> 31:47.625
[cell phone beeps]

31:47.625 --> 31:49.375
Dad?

31:49.375 --> 31:51.375
Hey.

31:51.375 --> 31:53.375
I'm gonna send you
an address.

31:53.375 --> 31:55.041
I need you to get
your friend

31:55.041 --> 31:56.083
and bring him there
in the morning, all right?

31:56.083 --> 31:58.458
- What's going on?
- We're gonna get him

31:58.458 --> 31:59.750
what he needs.

31:59.750 --> 32:00.417
I got to go.

32:00.417 --> 32:06.333
♪♪♪

32:13.500 --> 32:14.750
What's that?

32:14.750 --> 32:18.500
That's your fuckin'
boom stick.

32:24.041 --> 32:28.917
♪♪♪

32:28.917 --> 32:31.959
[keys jingle]

32:31.959 --> 32:33.875
Come on, Dog.
Come on!

32:33.875 --> 32:34.417
[smooches, whistles]

32:34.417 --> 32:39.083
♪♪♪

33:20.500 --> 33:22.583
Hey, Ray.

33:22.583 --> 33:24.291
Hey.

33:24.291 --> 33:25.750
What's up?

33:25.750 --> 33:26.667
[sighs]

33:26.667 --> 33:30.041
I changed my mind.

33:30.041 --> 33:31.667
About what?

33:31.667 --> 33:33.333
About the bar.

33:33.333 --> 33:37.834
I'm gonna call Harriet, tell
her to put it in your name.

33:37.834 --> 33:40.625
Well, how much
do you want for it?

33:43.041 --> 33:46.583
Nothing.
It's yours.

33:47.041 --> 33:50.083
What's going on?

33:54.208 --> 33:57.041
I got to go out of town
for a few days.

33:57.041 --> 33:59.333
Okay.

33:59.333 --> 34:04.083
I need you to, uh,
look after a dog for me.

34:06.750 --> 34:09.625
I've never...
watched the dog before.

34:14.375 --> 34:16.792
Did Ray just give you
the bar?

34:20.542 --> 34:22.083
Yeah.

34:24.709 --> 34:26.792
What about Pismo?

34:33.375 --> 34:35.250
Let me see her.

34:37.250 --> 34:39.750
- Come here, babe.
- [baby squeals softly]

34:39.750 --> 34:42.333
- [grunts] Ah, there ya go.
- [baby babbles]

34:45.583 --> 34:47.917
[whispers] Hey.

34:48.750 --> 34:50.750
Is that what you want?

34:50.750 --> 34:53.750
What I want...

34:56.208 --> 34:58.834
...is for you to go.

35:01.792 --> 35:04.792
Leave Maria with me.

35:07.917 --> 35:09.250
And you just go.

35:16.750 --> 35:19.333
Now let's see
what you got for me.

35:19.333 --> 35:21.542
Donovan, Mr. Holt's
ready to see you.

35:22.583 --> 35:25.083
Oh...

35:25.083 --> 35:26.709
yes.

35:26.709 --> 35:28.709
All right.

35:30.375 --> 35:32.125
Victor,
don't touch the cards.

35:32.125 --> 35:34.166
[Victor] All right.
Orale, gringo.

35:34.166 --> 35:36.750
I'm on the fucking verge.

35:40.291 --> 35:42.792
Jackson, I don't want to
put you guys out,

35:42.792 --> 35:44.083
but, uh, if we're talkin'
relocation,

35:44.083 --> 35:47.375
I'd love to go
somewhere quiet.

35:47.375 --> 35:49.792
They got, uh,
cabins out in Montana

35:49.792 --> 35:52.458
for a fucking song.

35:52.458 --> 35:55.959
Something by a lake maybe,
be good for my writing.

36:00.583 --> 36:03.208
[camera beeps]

36:03.208 --> 36:07.208
[buzzer sounds in distance]

36:07.208 --> 36:09.333
What do you think?

36:09.333 --> 36:11.959
I got a statement
from your son Daryll

36:11.959 --> 36:14.083
and your gun.

36:14.083 --> 36:16.000
The ballistics match.

36:21.166 --> 36:22.959
Whoa.

36:22.959 --> 36:27.083
You make a full confession
to the murder of Frank Barnes,

36:27.083 --> 36:28.291
confess to extorting
Jay White,

36:28.291 --> 36:32.500
and I don't go after
the death penalty.

36:32.500 --> 36:34.083
[smacks lips]
That's it?

36:34.083 --> 36:37.959
You make a full
confession,

36:37.959 --> 36:40.917
and I'll let you live out
the rest of your life

36:40.917 --> 36:42.500
in the elderly wing

36:42.500 --> 36:46.500
of one of our finest
state prisons.

36:46.500 --> 36:48.959
I see.

36:48.959 --> 36:51.542
So...

36:51.542 --> 36:53.500
what do you say?

36:53.500 --> 36:57.417
I say fuck yourself.
Do your worst.

36:58.917 --> 37:01.500
I'm going back.

37:01.500 --> 37:04.542
I was in the middle
of a game of solitaire

37:04.542 --> 37:06.333
I thought I might
actually win.

37:09.000 --> 37:12.208
[knock on door, buzzer sounds,
door opens]

37:12.208 --> 37:14.542
[Mickey] Going back.

37:14.542 --> 37:15.458
[door closes]

37:35.083 --> 37:38.750
[Sam] Is that
your daughter?

37:38.750 --> 37:40.250
What?

37:40.250 --> 37:43.625
You must really love her
to do all this.

37:43.625 --> 37:45.959
It's not my daughter.

37:52.250 --> 37:54.458
May I?

37:56.750 --> 37:57.375
[Sam] C'mon.

38:06.834 --> 38:09.291
[groans softly]

38:15.834 --> 38:18.333
Is this you?

38:21.917 --> 38:23.375
Yeah.

38:27.750 --> 38:29.834
Same eyes.

38:29.834 --> 38:32.041
Haunted.

38:32.041 --> 38:35.583
[chuckles]

38:35.583 --> 38:38.792
"Forgive yourself."

38:38.792 --> 38:41.333
Good luck with that.

38:43.125 --> 38:46.917
I tried to forgive myself.
Trust me, I tried.

38:46.917 --> 38:48.875
With...[sighs]

38:48.875 --> 38:51.667
...shrinks and...

38:51.667 --> 38:55.291
shamans and charlatans.

38:55.291 --> 38:57.166
L.A.'s lousy with 'em.

38:57.166 --> 39:00.583
How'd that work out
for you?

39:00.583 --> 39:03.917
At a certain point,
I realized...

39:05.583 --> 39:09.917
...I didn't really want
to forgive myself.

39:12.041 --> 39:15.500
We're only alive so long.

39:15.500 --> 39:17.333
We should just take
what we want

39:17.333 --> 39:20.125
and stop thinking
about it all the time.

39:20.125 --> 39:23.333
Stop waiting for permission.

39:26.959 --> 39:29.166
Don't you think?

39:29.166 --> 39:32.959
♪ dark music ♪

39:32.959 --> 39:38.125
♪♪♪

39:43.375 --> 39:46.375
[monitor beeping,
indistinct chatter]

39:51.208 --> 39:54.542
[chuckles painfully]

40:00.375 --> 40:03.083
Oh, I miss New York.

40:04.250 --> 40:07.709
I guess you'd prefer Boston.

40:07.709 --> 40:09.709
Not really.

40:09.709 --> 40:11.542
Really? Oh, I think
of Boston

40:11.542 --> 40:15.250
as a big ice cube
full of angry people.

40:15.250 --> 40:17.375
- [chuckles]
- That sounds right.

40:17.375 --> 40:19.709
[chuckles]

40:19.709 --> 40:22.917
♪♪♪

40:22.917 --> 40:25.083
Thank you.

40:25.083 --> 40:27.417
For doing this.

40:29.291 --> 40:32.625
We're friends.
That's what we do.

40:42.625 --> 40:45.000
This where you're staying?

40:45.000 --> 40:46.750
Nope.

40:46.750 --> 40:48.959
This is where Doug stays

40:48.959 --> 40:51.000
when he comes into town

40:51.000 --> 40:54.417
to tell the board
he's taking over my company.

40:56.000 --> 40:59.083
[whispering]
This is where Doug stays.

41:02.917 --> 41:05.625
All right, Hector,
on to the next stop.

41:05.625 --> 41:09.083
[Sam] And let's go
through the park.

41:09.083 --> 41:14.959
♪♪♪

41:17.291 --> 41:19.583
[indistinct chatter]

41:19.583 --> 41:20.750
[elevator bell dings]

41:24.625 --> 41:26.375
So you can get your
shoes shined,

41:26.375 --> 41:28.959
your taxes done,
and brain surgery

41:28.959 --> 41:32.166
all in one
convenient location.

41:32.166 --> 41:33.959
I love it.

41:33.959 --> 41:35.917
Hey.

41:35.917 --> 41:40.792
♪♪♪

41:40.792 --> 41:43.834
[monitor beeping,
indistinct chatter]

42:02.667 --> 42:04.583
Hi, Daddy.

42:04.583 --> 42:07.834
Thank you.
[breathes shakily]

42:07.834 --> 42:10.000
Sure.

42:11.750 --> 42:14.333
- [sniffles]
- Hey, come on.

42:14.333 --> 42:16.250
Ms. Winslow.

42:16.250 --> 42:18.333
Hi. Uh, I'm Bridget.

42:18.333 --> 42:20.709
Sam. So nice
to meet you.

42:20.709 --> 42:22.834
- Yeah.
- Well, you look a lot

42:22.834 --> 42:24.667
- like your dad.
- Oh, you think?

42:24.667 --> 42:26.458
In a much more
attractive way, of course.

42:26.458 --> 42:27.792
[laughs]

42:27.792 --> 42:30.417
And you must be
a Donovan.

42:30.417 --> 42:32.083
- Terry.
- Terry.

42:32.083 --> 42:35.041
- Sam. So nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

42:35.041 --> 42:37.709
Well, it seems like
everything's under control here.

42:40.875 --> 42:43.667
- [Bridget] Nice to meet you.
- [Sam] Nice to meet you.

42:43.667 --> 42:46.792
Everyone doesn't get
a father like yours.

42:50.500 --> 42:51.917
I'll walk you
to your car.

42:51.917 --> 42:53.667
No, it's not necessary.

42:53.667 --> 42:55.917
[sighs] What did you
have to do

42:55.917 --> 42:57.709
to make this happen?

42:58.458 --> 43:01.542
It doesn't matter.
It's done.

43:01.542 --> 43:04.542
♪ solemn music ♪

43:04.542 --> 43:08.750
♪♪♪

43:19.959 --> 43:20.834
Beckett.

43:23.959 --> 43:25.250
I'm making a list.

43:25.250 --> 43:29.166
[door closes]

43:30.625 --> 43:34.083
I'm gonna make
a few changes around here.

43:34.083 --> 43:35.959
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

43:35.959 --> 43:38.583
Bring in some entertainment--

43:38.583 --> 43:41.583
foosball, pinball,

43:41.583 --> 43:43.750
darts, you know?

43:43.750 --> 43:45.417
Make the place
a little more lively.

43:45.417 --> 43:48.125
Did you say "pinball"?

43:48.125 --> 43:50.083
Yeah.

43:51.458 --> 43:54.417
I'm a pinball wizard.

43:54.417 --> 43:56.333
Oh, yeah?

43:56.333 --> 44:00.875
I scored 178 million
playing Addams Family.

44:00.875 --> 44:02.625
You like Addams Family?

44:02.625 --> 44:04.625
What the Mona Lisa
was to the Renaissance

44:04.625 --> 44:08.667
Addams Family
is to pinball machines.

44:10.375 --> 44:12.667
Okay.

44:12.667 --> 44:16.917
So we get that.
Fuck it, I got the money.

44:16.917 --> 44:19.500
- Rad.
- Yeah.

44:19.500 --> 44:21.750
Addams Family,
Twilight Zone,

44:21.750 --> 44:25.959
Ghostbusters--
fuck it, we'll get 'em all.

44:27.458 --> 44:29.667
Hell to the yeah, man.

44:33.875 --> 44:35.834
[woman speaks indistinctly]

44:35.834 --> 44:38.875
All right, Christina, get in
there with that retractor.

44:38.875 --> 44:41.208
And I just get that needle
right in there.

44:41.208 --> 44:43.333
Okay. That's good.

44:43.333 --> 44:44.417
- All right.
- Get ready, Doc.

44:44.417 --> 44:48.000
[monitors beeping]

44:48.000 --> 44:49.333
Here we go.

44:49.333 --> 44:51.583
[man] Push it.

44:51.583 --> 44:53.500
[woman] Good, good, good.

44:53.500 --> 44:58.250
♪♪♪

45:08.208 --> 45:11.125
Abby was so far gone, Ray.

45:14.667 --> 45:17.041
She was in so much pain.

45:21.792 --> 45:24.375
Things got messed up.

45:28.375 --> 45:31.542
I didn't mean for things
to get messed up.

45:43.291 --> 45:45.417
[sighs]

45:46.375 --> 45:49.041
You'll stick around?

45:49.041 --> 45:51.458
What?

45:51.458 --> 45:53.417
For Bridget.

45:54.583 --> 45:56.709
You'll stick around
for Bridget?

45:56.709 --> 45:59.500
What are you talking about?

46:00.583 --> 46:03.375
♪ Dramatic music ♪

46:03.375 --> 46:05.875
Where you going?

46:05.875 --> 46:08.917
[indistinct chatter]

46:08.917 --> 46:13.500
♪♪♪

46:49.917 --> 46:52.083
[elevator bell dings]

47:05.625 --> 47:08.125
[elevator bell dings]

47:18.750 --> 47:21.000
[Doug] I know, it's--
it's heartbreaking, isn't it?

47:31.000 --> 47:32.500
[scoffs]

47:32.500 --> 47:37.083
You had a funeral viewing
party with Aunt Dot?

47:37.083 --> 47:38.834
[champagne pouring]

47:38.834 --> 47:40.125
[chuckles]

47:42.834 --> 47:45.417
Yes, it was a new suit.

47:50.750 --> 47:55.500
Oh, okay, well, I deposited
a check for you, uh, last week.

47:55.500 --> 47:58.125
No, in your savings.

47:58.125 --> 48:02.792
Not your checking, Mom,
in your savings.

48:04.125 --> 48:08.166
Well, you can transfer it
into your checking.

48:12.166 --> 48:15.333
Cheryl's great.
She's with the kids in Idaho.

48:19.542 --> 48:22.917
Uh, we had a fund-raiser
at the house last week.

48:22.917 --> 48:24.166
[clears throat]
Yeah, the same.

48:24.166 --> 48:27.875
The low-cost-housing
initiative in Jakarta.

48:28.709 --> 48:31.375
I know. I'm very proud
of her, too.

48:31.375 --> 48:33.291
♪ ominous music ♪

48:33.291 --> 48:36.333
I am. I'm taking
very good care of myself.

48:36.333 --> 48:38.208
♪♪♪

48:38.208 --> 48:41.792
Okay, well, you give yourself
a big hug from me.

48:41.792 --> 48:43.250
♪♪♪

48:43.250 --> 48:46.083
Okay. Bye.

48:46.083 --> 48:46.500
Bye.

48:46.500 --> 48:50.458
[choking]

48:50.458 --> 48:53.625
♪ tense music ♪

48:53.625 --> 48:58.792
♪♪♪

49:05.125 --> 49:07.667
He's out of surgery.
You can see him soon.

49:07.667 --> 49:09.750
How'd it go?

49:09.750 --> 49:12.000
We met all our markers.
I liked what I saw.

49:12.000 --> 49:13.375
We'll see what's next.

49:16.041 --> 49:18.333
Thank you.

49:18.333 --> 49:20.250
He'll need, uh,
several days of home care.

49:20.250 --> 49:21.041
There's a list
of all the meds,

49:21.041 --> 49:23.250
all the things
to watch for.

49:31.792 --> 49:33.291
All right?

49:33.291 --> 49:34.542
- [whispers] Yeah.
- Yeah?

49:34.542 --> 49:36.959
Yeah, I'm good.

49:36.959 --> 49:37.583
- [inhales shakily]
- Come on.

49:37.583 --> 49:39.083
All right.

49:44.792 --> 49:48.583
♪ somber music ♪

49:48.583 --> 49:53.709
♪♪♪

50:00.041 --> 50:02.250
[siren wailing in distance]

50:54.667 --> 50:59.792
♪♪♪

52:11.959 --> 52:15.166
[siren wailing in distance]

52:21.792 --> 52:25.709
[lighter clicks]

52:56.959 --> 52:59.834
♪ David Bowie's
"Rock and Roll Suicide" plays ♪

52:59.834 --> 53:05.000
♪♪♪

53:10.083 --> 53:14.834
♪ Time takes a cigarette ♪

53:14.834 --> 53:18.458
♪ Puts it in your mouth ♪

53:18.458 --> 53:20.041
♪ You pull on your finger ♪

53:20.041 --> 53:23.000
♪ Then another finger ♪

53:23.000 --> 53:25.667
♪ Then cigarette ♪

53:25.667 --> 53:28.500
♪ The wall-to-wall
is calling ♪

53:28.500 --> 53:32.417
♪ It lingers,
then you forget ♪

53:32.417 --> 53:35.208
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

53:35.208 --> 53:38.041
♪ You're
a rock and roll suicide ♪

53:38.041 --> 53:41.083
♪♪♪

53:41.083 --> 53:44.542
♪ You're too old
to lose it ♪

53:44.542 --> 53:48.417
♪ Too young to choose it ♪

53:48.417 --> 53:52.333
♪ And the clock waits
so patiently ♪

53:52.333 --> 53:55.500
♪ On your song ♪

53:55.500 --> 53:57.750
♪ You walk past the café ♪

53:57.750 --> 54:01.917
♪ But you don't eat
when you've lived too long ♪

54:01.917 --> 54:05.041
♪ Oh, no, no, no ♪

54:05.041 --> 54:06.208
♪ You're
a rock and roll suicide ♪

54:06.208 --> 54:08.083
[buzzer sounds]

54:08.083 --> 54:10.500
♪♪♪

54:10.500 --> 54:12.333
♪ Chev brakes are snarlin' ♪

54:12.333 --> 54:16.250
♪ As you stumble
across the road ♪

54:16.250 --> 54:18.000
♪♪♪

54:18.000 --> 54:20.458
♪ But the day breaks
instead ♪

54:20.458 --> 54:23.375
♪ So you hurry home ♪

54:23.375 --> 54:27.917
♪ Don't let the sun
blast your shadow ♪

54:27.917 --> 54:31.291
♪ Don't let the milk float
ride your mind ♪

54:31.291 --> 54:33.125
♪ You're so natural ♪

54:33.125 --> 54:36.458
♪ Religiously unkind ♪

54:36.458 --> 54:38.834
♪ Oh, no, love,
you're not alone ♪

54:38.834 --> 54:41.083
Hi, sweetheart.

54:41.083 --> 54:44.959
♪ You're watching yourself,
but you're too unfair ♪

54:44.959 --> 54:47.792
♪ You've got your head
all tangled up ♪

54:47.792 --> 54:51.417
♪ But if I can only
make you care ♪

54:51.417 --> 54:55.291
♪ Oh, no, love,
you're not alone ♪

54:55.291 --> 54:58.125
♪ No matter
what a fool you've been ♪

54:58.125 --> 55:00.709
♪ No matter when
or where you've seen ♪

55:00.709 --> 55:04.959
♪ All the knives
seem to lacerate your brain ♪

55:04.959 --> 55:06.333
♪ I've had my share ♪

55:06.333 --> 55:09.542
♪ I'll help you
with the pain ♪

55:09.542 --> 55:10.792
♪ You're not alone ♪

55:10.792 --> 55:14.000
♪♪♪

55:14.000 --> 55:16.041
♪ Just turn on with me ♪

55:16.041 --> 55:19.166
♪ And you're not alone ♪

55:19.166 --> 55:21.166
♪♪♪

55:21.166 --> 55:23.959
♪ Let's turn on and be ♪

55:23.959 --> 55:24.959
- ♪ Not alone ♪
- ♪ Wonderful ♪

55:24.959 --> 55:27.834
♪♪♪

55:27.834 --> 55:29.959
♪ Give me your hands ♪

55:29.959 --> 55:32.125
- ♪ 'Cause you're wonderful ♪
- ♪ Wonderful ♪

55:32.125 --> 55:34.500
♪♪♪

55:34.500 --> 55:35.792
♪ Give me your hands ♪

55:35.792 --> 55:38.792
- ♪ 'Cause you're wonderful ♪
- ♪ Wonderful ♪

55:38.792 --> 55:40.959
♪♪♪

55:40.959 --> 55:43.417
♪ Oh, give me your hands ♪

55:43.417 --> 55:46.166
[music swells]

55:46.166 --> 55:48.875
♪♪♪

55:48.875 --> 55:52.417
[end chords]

56:00.709 --> 56:03.709
♪ somber music ♪

56:03.709 --> 56:08.625
♪♪♪
